250
00:15:51,520 --> 00:15:55,280
Fedens, I know you
have heard many things.

251
00:15:56,240 --> 00:15:58,160
And I know
what we have seen, Thomas.

252
00:15:58,240 --> 00:16:00,880
But please, the United Nations
are here now.

253
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:03,400
The world press are watching.

254
00:16:03,400 --> 00:16:06,120
The peace has been signed.
Let this process work--

255
00:16:06,200 --> 00:16:07,680
What was that?

256
00:16:11,840 --> 00:16:13,120
Power cuts.

257
00:16:14,360 --> 00:16:16,400
We are running on generators.

258
00:16:17,360 --> 00:16:19,280
Fedens...

259
00:16:19,280 --> 00:16:20,880
Please, don't worry.

260
00:16:22,800 --> 00:16:26,560
Tomorrow you will come by the house
and we will discuss this with Tatiana.

261
00:16:26,600 --> 00:16:27,920
All right?

262
00:16:30,440 --> 00:16:33,320
- Good night, Paul.
- Yes. Kiss the girls for me.

263
00:17:00,720 --> 00:17:01,960
Shit!

264
00:17:15,520 --> 00:17:18,320
Stay in your houses.
Stay in your house.

265
00:17:18,400 --> 00:17:20,520
Everybody stay in your house!

266
00:17:50,840 --> 00:17:51,960
Tatiana?

267
00:18:20,680 --> 00:18:22,760
- Paul!
- Tatiana!

268
00:18:24,360 --> 00:18:26,840
- What is going on here?
- Our house has been burned.

269
00:18:27,400 --> 00:18:29,640
- Didn't you hear the news?
- What news?

270
00:18:29,720 --> 00:18:32,920
They are saying President Habyarimana
has been murdered.

271
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:34,720
Tutsi rebels have killed him.

272
00:18:34,760 --> 00:18:38,000
Nonsense. Why would the rebels kill
the president when he agreed to peace?

273
00:18:41,160 --> 00:18:43,760
Everyone, please.
out of this room. Please.

274
00:18:43,880 --> 00:18:45,800
Jean Baptiste, find them seats
in the other room.

275
00:18:45,880 --> 00:18:47,600
Odette, please.

276
00:18:50,800 --> 00:18:54,720
- Did you meet with Thomas and Fedens?
- Yes, I told them to go home.

277
00:18:55,800 --> 00:18:59,240
- Go and call them, Tatsi.

278
00:19:03,360 --> 00:19:07,200
- Why do the neighbors run to us?
- You are the only Hutu they can trust.

279
00:19:07,320 --> 00:19:08,800
You are a Tutsi.

280
00:19:08,880 --> 00:19:12,000
They are scared, Paul.
I am scared.

281
00:19:18,120 --> 00:19:20,840
These are probably rumors
started by agitators.

282
00:19:20,920 --> 00:19:23,600
We must remain calm
for the children, Tatsi. We must.

283
00:19:24,040 --> 00:19:27,480
Forgive me, Paul.
Elys says that Roger has gone.

284
00:19:27,560 --> 00:19:29,720
Gone? Gone where?

285
00:19:29,720 --> 00:19:33,320
- He was afraid for his friend Simon, Mama.

286
00:19:33,400 --> 00:19:34,440
He went next door.

287
00:19:35,400 --> 00:19:37,080
Wait, Paul!

288
00:19:37,160 --> 00:19:40,120
Tatiana, no, You have to

289
00:19:40,200 --> 00:19:41,960
- Stay in the house, No!
- Please.

290
00:19:49,520 --> 00:19:52,800
Paul, please, what is wrong?
Tell me, what is wrong?

291
00:19:52,920 --> 00:19:55,800
- Oh, my son! Where are you hurt?
- Is he okay? Oh, my baby!

292
00:19:55,880 --> 00:19:57,880
Talk to me.
Where are you hurt?

293
00:19:57,960 --> 00:19:59,000
Paul?

294
00:20:01,560 --> 00:20:02,680
Oh, Tatsi.

295
00:20:04,880 --> 00:20:06,800
Odette, Odette!

296
00:20:06,880 --> 00:20:07,840
Oh, no.

297
00:20:07,920 --> 00:20:09,320
I'm okay.

298
00:20:09,400 --> 00:20:11,680
Get his clothes off.
Tatsi, please get some water.

299
00:20:11,760 --> 00:20:13,840
- He's hurt.
- Please, let's get his clothes off.

300
00:20:13,920 --> 00:20:16,240
- He's covered in blood.
- Lay back, son.

301
00:20:17,920 --> 00:20:19,840
He went next door
to the Chirangas.

302
00:20:20,720 --> 00:20:22,400
Where is he hurt?

303
00:20:22,960 --> 00:20:24,880
Look here, Odette, look here.

304
00:20:25,040 --> 00:20:27,520
Stay still, Roger.
Keep him still, Paul.

305
00:20:28,320 --> 00:20:30,800
- I can't find the wound.
- What happened to you?

306
00:20:30,880 --> 00:20:32,280
- Tell your mother.
- Talk to me.

307
00:20:32,320 --> 00:20:34,360
Tell your mother
what happened, Roger.

308
00:20:34,440 --> 00:20:35,840
Roger, you're okay.

309
00:20:35,840 --> 00:20:39,520
Do not worry, he is not cut.
He is not hurt.

310
00:20:39,600 --> 00:20:41,960
This is not his blood, Paul.

311
00:20:43,160 --> 00:20:44,480
You are not hurt.

312
00:20:44,480 --> 00:20:47,880
My darling, it's okay.
It's okay.

313
00:20:47,920 --> 00:20:49,720
You are safe.
Look at your mother.

314
00:20:49,800 --> 00:20:51,760
Come here, Elys.

315
00:20:51,760 --> 00:20:55,200
- Where did the blood come from?
- Please, please!

316
00:20:56,080 --> 00:20:57,920
- You are safe.
- You are out, Roger.

317
00:20:58,000 --> 00:21:00,640
You are safe, you are safe, Roger.
You are safe, Roger.

318
00:21:00,720 --> 00:21:02,240
It's okay.

319
00:21:02,320 --> 00:21:04,480
I love you so much.
I love you.

320
00:21:23,520 --> 00:21:24,760
Oh, son.

321
00:21:29,040 --> 00:21:30,440
Paul.

322
00:21:30,440 --> 00:21:35,720
Listen to me, good people of Rwanda.
Terrible news...

323
00:21:35,800 --> 00:21:38,680
- It is true.
- Horrible news...

324
00:21:38,760 --> 00:21:43,320
Our great president
is murdered by the Tutsi cockroaches.

325
00:21:43,320 --> 00:21:44,280
Oh, my God!

326
00:21:44,360 --> 00:21:48,040
They tricked him to sign
their phony peace agreement.

327
00:21:48,120 --> 00:21:50,640
Then they shot his plane
from the sky.

328
00:21:51,600 --> 00:21:55,800
It is time to clear the brush.
good Hutus of Rwanda.

329
00:21:56,840 --> 00:21:59,560
We must cut the tall trees.

330
00:22:00,160 --> 00:22:02,880
cut the tall trees now!

331
00:22:02,960 --> 00:22:04,440
The soldiers are here!

332
00:22:04,520 --> 00:22:07,320
- Let us go to work, loyal Hutus.
- No, no.

333
00:22:07,400 --> 00:22:09,840
Everyone, stay calm.
Stay calm and be quiet.

334
00:22:09,920 --> 00:22:14,160
Find these traitors.
Let none of them escape.

335
00:22:15,040 --> 00:22:17,680
Split up.
Everybody out.

336
00:22:19,680 --> 00:22:22,080
- You two, check the back.

337
00:22:23,680 --> 00:22:26,000
- You, go and find him.
- Yes, sir.

338
00:22:31,960 --> 00:22:33,880
I better go have a word with them.

339
00:22:35,200 --> 00:22:37,800
Go around the back.
Make sure no one comes out.

340
00:22:37,920 --> 00:22:38,880
Yes, sir!

341
00:22:40,360 --> 00:22:42,440
Who's in charge here?

342
00:22:42,520 --> 00:22:43,680
You.

343
00:22:49,320 --> 00:22:52,120
- Can I help you, sir?
- Everybody out! Out!

344
00:22:52,200 --> 00:22:55,000
- Let me see your identity card.
- Grab your things. Go!

345
00:22:55,080 --> 00:22:57,000
I am a good friend
of General Bizimungu.

346
00:22:57,120 --> 00:22:58,120
Get out!

347
00:23:01,640 --> 00:23:03,480
Get out of here!

348
00:23:03,560 --> 00:23:05,800
Everybody, out!
Get out, get out!

349
00:23:05,880 --> 00:23:07,400
You work at the Hotel Diplomat?

350
00:23:08,840 --> 00:23:10,520
No, I work at the Mille Collines.

351
00:23:12,160 --> 00:23:13,960
I used to work at the Diplomat.

352
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:16,600
We want to use that hotel.
All the room keys are in the safe.

353
00:23:16,720 --> 00:23:18,960
You must open it.
Let's go.

354
00:23:19,040 --> 00:23:22,440
- Paul!
- Sir, I cannot leave my family.

355
00:23:22,560 --> 00:23:25,160
I must take them with me.
It is not safe here.

356
00:23:25,240 --> 00:23:27,280
There are Tutsi spies everywhere.

357
00:23:27,360 --> 00:23:28,920
I cannot take all these people.

358
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:30,880
No, no, sir.

359
00:23:30,960 --> 00:23:33,680
We have our car
and our van.

360
00:23:33,680 --> 00:23:36,320
- Captain Kaliso, come on.
- Roger.

361
00:23:36,840 --> 00:23:40,720
- Let's go!
- Come on. Hurry! Go around, go around.

362
00:23:40,800 --> 00:23:42,960
We found him.
Let's go. Let's go!

363
00:23:44,320 --> 00:23:47,600
- Can I go with you?
- Yes, of course, Jeremiah. Hurry.

364
00:23:57,400 --> 00:23:58,920
Oh, Jesus, no!

365
00:24:00,720 --> 00:24:02,200
Oh, it's Simon, Papa!

366
00:24:03,280 --> 00:24:06,320
Don't look, don't look, don't look.

367
00:25:08,120 --> 00:25:10,920
- The safe is in the manager's office.
- You two, go with him.

368
00:25:18,880 --> 00:25:21,160
Look at this. Beer.

369
00:25:37,600 --> 00:25:38,800
I've got them.

370
00:25:50,000 --> 00:25:51,400
Get down, all of you!

371
00:25:57,160 --> 00:26:00,920
Sir, sir. Here, I have them.

372
00:26:05,440 --> 00:26:07,200
Traitor!

373
00:26:07,280 --> 00:26:09,120
These are Tutsi cockroaches!

374
00:26:09,800 --> 00:26:12,120
Let me explain, sir.
Please wait.

375
00:26:15,320 --> 00:26:16,360
Shoot them.

376
00:26:17,720 --> 00:26:18,840
Shoot them.

377
00:26:20,600 --> 00:26:24,120
Please, I don't use guns.
I don't.

378
00:26:24,160 --> 00:26:25,120
It's easy.

379
00:26:29,920 --> 00:26:33,080
Shoot them, or you die first.

380
00:26:33,960 --> 00:26:37,520
Sir, what could I pay you
not to do this?

381
00:26:37,600 --> 00:26:39,360
You wanna pay me?

382
00:26:39,360 --> 00:26:41,720
Why not?
Look at them.

383
00:26:41,800 --> 00:26:43,560
These are not rebels.

384
00:26:44,520 --> 00:26:47,840
Soon they will be worthless to you.
Why not take some money for your work?

385
00:26:47,920 --> 00:26:50,360
- How much?
- You name a price.

386
00:26:57,920 --> 00:26:59,600
10,000 francs for each.

387
00:27:00,480 --> 00:27:02,960
- Sir, I don't have that much.

388
00:27:03,080 --> 00:27:05,000
Wait, wait! Here.

389
00:27:05,040 --> 00:27:08,280
It's 1,000 U,S.

390
00:27:09,040 --> 00:27:11,760
50,000 francs for my wife and children.

391
00:27:11,840 --> 00:27:13,880
- Take them.
- Go, go, go.

392
00:27:13,960 --> 00:27:16,240
Go, go, go.

393
00:27:16,320 --> 00:27:18,160
- Have you any money?
- Nothing.

394
00:27:18,240 --> 00:27:21,320
- Paul, don't let them die.

395
00:27:26,200 --> 00:27:28,960
Sir, I have more money actually.

396
00:27:30,760 --> 00:27:33,960
And let them give you something.
Some money, whatever they have.

397
00:27:34,040 --> 00:27:35,080
All right?

398
00:27:36,520 --> 00:27:38,680
Here you are.
Give me everything you have.

399
00:27:40,760 --> 00:27:42,520
Here, Paul, it's all I have.

400
00:27:45,400 --> 00:27:47,480
Here you are. See?

401
00:27:49,320 --> 00:27:52,200
This is enough for one cockroach.
Pick one.

402
00:27:53,720 --> 00:27:54,880
Sir...

403
00:27:56,960 --> 00:28:00,200
I will give you 100,000 francs
for all of them.

404
00:28:02,120 --> 00:28:03,920
- Give me it.
- I don't have it here.

405
00:28:04,040 --> 00:28:05,960
At the Mille Collines
I can get it for you.

406
00:28:06,040 --> 00:28:08,320
You'll run into the hotel
and hide behind the U,N.

407
00:28:08,400 --> 00:28:12,880
Sir, I swear.

408
00:28:12,960 --> 00:28:16,320
I will get you the money.
You keep them outside.

409
00:28:18,880 --> 00:28:20,960
Please, sir. Please.

410
00:28:22,240 --> 00:28:24,720
- Let's go.
- Okay. Everyone in the van.

411
00:28:24,800 --> 00:28:26,400
Come on now. Hurry.

412
00:28:37,680 --> 00:28:41,320
Go with my soldiers. And hurry back
if you want to keep these cockroaches.

413
00:28:45,800 --> 00:28:48,440
The soldiers are here.
Where is the car?

414
00:28:48,440 --> 00:28:51,720
There is nothing I can do.
Excuse me, sir! Please, could you--

415
00:29:03,560 --> 00:29:04,920
Here's the money.

416
00:29:04,920 --> 00:29:07,360
100,000 francs as promised.

417
00:29:07,440 --> 00:29:09,360
Now please, let them go, sir.

418
00:29:09,360 --> 00:29:11,520
Take the money.
We will get them later.

419
00:29:14,240 --> 00:29:16,320
- You can go.
- Thank you.

420
00:29:18,360 --> 00:29:19,400
Traitor.

421
00:29:23,840 --> 00:29:25,040
Thank you, Paul.

422
00:29:30,280 --> 00:29:33,080
Do you understand, Dube?
Because I can't wait for Paul.

423
00:29:33,080 --> 00:29:35,320
- You must tell him when he comes--
- Here he is, sir.

424
00:29:36,840 --> 00:29:40,760
Paul, I have to go.
The staff of Kivu Lodge have fled.

425
00:29:40,840 --> 00:29:43,640
I have to close up there.
You are in charge now.

426
00:29:43,720 --> 00:29:44,840
It's okay, it's okay.

427
00:29:44,840 --> 00:29:48,480
There were no survivors in last night's
plane crash in Kigali, Rwanda.

428
00:29:48,480 --> 00:29:51,200
Everyone, please move to the side.
Clear the door.

429
00:29:51,280 --> 00:29:52,600
Come, Tatsi.

430
00:29:54,920 --> 00:29:56,960
Andre, I need two suites.

431
00:29:57,040 --> 00:29:59,320
- Paul, please, where is my passport?
- Yes, I understand.

432
00:29:59,320 --> 00:30:03,320
- I need to get hold of my embassy.
- If you give me one moment, please.

433
00:30:04,640 --> 00:30:08,200
- Odette, Jean Baptiste, take this room.
- What about our neighbors?

434
00:30:09,360 --> 00:30:10,840
What will they do?

435
00:30:13,280 --> 00:30:15,560
- Dube.
- Yes, sir?

436
00:30:17,120 --> 00:30:21,280
Please put these "guests"
in two staff rooms.

437
00:30:21,360 --> 00:30:22,800
Right away, sir.

438
00:30:31,120 --> 00:30:34,160
No, no, no. Please, it's old.

439
00:30:37,960 --> 00:30:40,480
It's all right, Roger.
It's all right. We're here.

440
00:30:41,680 --> 00:30:43,280
- Ah, Joseph.
- Your suit, sir.

441
00:30:43,360 --> 00:30:44,680
This mess is unacceptable.

442
00:30:44,680 --> 00:30:47,640
Call housekeeping, get them
up here right away. Thank you.

443
00:30:49,640 --> 00:30:51,800
- I'm trying Thomas and Fedens.
- All right.

444
00:30:54,360 --> 00:30:56,760
Operator, I need a line.

445
00:30:56,840 --> 00:30:59,560
I need a line now. Please. Hello?

446
00:31:04,200 --> 00:31:06,280
You did not reach them?

447
00:31:06,360 --> 00:31:08,440
No. No answer.

448
00:31:09,880 --> 00:31:13,440
It is a very tense situation,
and I just want to assure the families

449
00:31:13,480 --> 00:31:16,480
of those who are there that we are
doing everything we possibly can

450
00:31:16,560 --> 00:31:19,000
to try to ensure
the safety of our citizens there.

451
00:31:19,080 --> 00:31:21,200
Can you at least tell us.
is the airport actually open?

452
00:31:21,280 --> 00:31:23,880
We are calling the airport.
We are calling the embassy.

453
00:31:23,960 --> 00:31:26,440
We are trying to get as much
information for you as we can.

454
00:31:26,520 --> 00:31:28,240
- And yes, your passport, yes.
- And my passport.

455
00:31:28,360 --> 00:31:30,560
Antoinette will take care
of this for you.

456
00:31:32,360 --> 00:31:34,720
Dube, where is Gregoire?

457
00:31:37,040 --> 00:31:40,320
Sir, he has moved

458
00:31:54,400 --> 00:31:55,520
Mr. Manager.

459
00:31:57,360 --> 00:31:59,280
What do you think
you are doing, Gregoire?

460
00:31:59,360 --> 00:32:00,680
Who is it?

461
00:32:01,400 --> 00:32:02,880
It's okay, darling.

462
00:32:03,560 --> 00:32:04,880
What do you want?

463
00:32:04,960 --> 00:32:08,360
You had better get out of this room
and back downstairs right away.

464
00:32:08,360 --> 00:32:11,520
- I don't have to listen to you anymore.
- Yes, you do.

465
00:32:11,600 --> 00:32:14,600
I am in charge. Now get out
of this room right now.

466
00:32:20,440 --> 00:32:24,800
Mr. Manager, do you notice
the smell of cockroaches?

467
00:32:26,360 --> 00:32:29,240
If I were to leave this room.

468
00:32:29,960 --> 00:32:32,320
And I know people
who can cleanse it.

469
00:32:33,560 --> 00:32:37,120
But maybe it doesn't bother you.
Why is that?

470
00:32:38,520 --> 00:32:40,280
Are you used to the smell?

471
00:32:41,760 --> 00:32:42,960
Well, not me.

472
00:32:43,920 --> 00:32:46,200
I need a clean room
to escape it.

473
00:32:52,200 --> 00:32:55,840
Please move into the hotel.
Everyone, keep moving.

474
00:32:55,840 --> 00:32:58,160
My house has been burned.
I have nowhere to go.

475
00:32:58,240 --> 00:32:59,680
Yes, I understand this, Your Honor.

476
00:32:59,760 --> 00:33:01,920
But we are operating
at capacity as it is.

477
00:33:02,000 --> 00:33:05,680
I can give you one room.
but you will have to share it, I'm sorry.

478
00:33:05,760 --> 00:33:08,240
- There's no way we can share.
- I am sorry. Forgive me.

479
00:33:08,320 --> 00:33:09,760
There are eight of us.

480
00:33:09,760 --> 00:33:11,280
- Yes?
- Paul, I need your help.

481
00:33:11,400 --> 00:33:12,480
Yes, Madame Archer.

482
00:33:19,680 --> 00:33:22,360
They're Tutsi children
from the St. Francis orphanage.

483
00:33:22,880 --> 00:33:24,560
Okay, come on, let's go.

484
00:33:25,160 --> 00:33:28,000
- I have only one room.
- That'll do.

485
00:33:30,160 --> 00:33:31,600
Come.

486
00:33:31,680 --> 00:33:33,920
- Otto, please.
- Excuse me.

487
00:33:35,000 --> 00:33:37,880
Corporal, take that lady's bag, please.
and quickly.

488
00:33:40,400 --> 00:33:43,680
- Have to go get the rest of them.
- The rest of them?

489
00:33:43,760 --> 00:33:46,000
There are another ten.
I'll be back soon.

490
00:33:48,480 --> 00:33:50,320
Madame Archer.

491
00:33:50,400 --> 00:33:52,040
I have a favor to ask of you.

492
00:33:52,120 --> 00:33:55,560
My brother-in-law and his family.
they live near the St. Francis.

493
00:33:55,600 --> 00:33:57,640
On O'Clare, 20.

494
00:33:57,720 --> 00:34:00,520
Can you please get them
and bring them here to me?

495
00:34:00,600 --> 00:34:02,520
- Sure.
- And I have a photo.

496
00:34:04,440 --> 00:34:06,120
Please, keep moving!

497
00:34:09,680 --> 00:34:11,240
- Thanks, Paul.

498
00:34:11,320 --> 00:34:13,080
Please move into the hotel!

499
00:34:13,160 --> 00:34:14,760
Come on, kids, don't be afraid.

500
00:34:14,840 --> 00:34:17,400
- Take them around the back.
- Everyone, keep moving!

501
00:34:23,080 --> 00:34:25,400
Has he spoken to you yet?

502
00:34:25,480 --> 00:34:26,440
No.

503
00:34:39,560 --> 00:34:41,560
Is your face still hurting?

504
00:34:42,560 --> 00:34:43,680
It's all right.

505
00:34:49,960 --> 00:34:52,560
The neighbors asked me
to thank you for your kindness.

506
00:34:55,200 --> 00:34:57,200
I shouldn't have brought them here.

507
00:34:59,120 --> 00:35:02,320
The first thing they told me
when I received my appointment

508
00:35:02,320 --> 00:35:05,000
was to never, never lower

509
00:35:06,400 --> 00:35:09,200
"Maintain the Mille Collines' dignity
at all times, Paul,"

510
00:35:13,840 --> 00:35:15,760
Soon all of this will be over.

511
00:35:18,120 --> 00:35:20,200
What if I lose my job, Tatsi?

512
00:35:23,080 --> 00:35:24,040
Oh, my God!

513
00:35:24,120 --> 00:35:26,240
- Where are you going?
- I'll be right back.

514
00:35:45,560 --> 00:35:47,400
Take care of them.

515
00:35:47,480 --> 00:35:48,720
How, sir?

516
00:35:49,920 --> 00:35:52,360
Bathe them, feed them.

517
00:35:53,760 --> 00:35:55,000
Put them to bed.

518
00:35:58,040 --> 00:35:59,600
I will send you some help.

519
00:36:04,240 --> 00:36:05,960
Okay, babies.

520
00:36:06,240 --> 00:36:08,440
